            "answer_text": "Question: How do I prove if a union b=a union c and a intersection b=a intersection c, then can you prove that b=c? Answer: Let me rephrase the question as follows: Prove that B = C given AUB = AUC and AnB = AnC Proof: Let x be an arbitrary element in B So x is in AUB (as B is a subset of AUB) So x is in AUC (as AUB = AUC) So x is in A or x is in C If x is in C, then we are done So let x be in A So x is in AnB (as x was originally in B, not it is in A as well) So x is in AnC (as AnB = AnC) So x is in C (as AnC is a subset of C) As x was an arbitrary element of B, B is a subset of C Similarly C is a subset of B Hence, B = C (as both are subsets of each other) ",
