            "answer_text": "n(A U B) = n(A U C) \u2026\u2026.1 n(A \u2229 B) = n(A \u2229 C)\u2026\u2026\u20262 Expanding equation 1 n(A) + n(B) \u2014 n( A \u2229 B) = n(A) + n(C) \u2014 n(A\u2229C)\u20263 Substituting 2 in equation 3 n(A) + n(B) \u2014 n(A\u2229B) = n(A) + n(C) \u2014 n(A\u2229 B) Therefore n(B) = n(C) ",
